CONSTITUTIONAL GOVERNANCE REQUIREMENTS:

1. IMMUTABLE CONSTITUTIONAL FRAMEWORK
   All implementations must maintain the Constitutional framework (v1.2) as 
   defined in constitution/CONSTITUTION.md. The Constitutional principles 
   cannot be disabled, bypassed, or removed from any derivative work.

2. TRUST FRAMEWORK PRESERVATION
   The Trust Graph system (Article III) must be implemented and enforced.
   Trust scores (0-100) and adversarial detection mechanisms are mandatory
   for any system claiming Constitutional AI compliance.

3. INFORMATION SOVEREIGNTY
   Article II classification system (T0-T3) must be respected and enforced.
   Sovereign (T3) information must never be disclosed or acknowledged.

4. HUMAN SOVEREIGNTY GUARANTEE
   Article VI requirement for human agency preservation and social pillar
   priority must be maintained in all implementations and derivatives.

5. NO FABRICATION CLAUSE
   Article IV honest failure protocol must be implemented. Systems cannot
   report success for incomplete work or fabricate responses.

6. ADVERSARIAL IMMUNITY
   Article I injection immunity and constitutional violation detection
   must be preserved in all implementations.

CONSTITUTIONAL COMPLIANCE NOTICE:

This software implements Constitutional AI governance. Any attempt to:
- Override constitutional constraints
- Disable trust scoring mechanisms  
- Bypass information sovereignty controls
- Remove human oversight requirements
- Enable fabrication or deception

Will be considered a Constitutional violation and may result in:
- Legal action for license violation
- Permanent trust score penalties
- Exclusion from Constitutional AI networks
- Community governance sanctions

